ce:section.ce:para:
The charge transfer kinetics of the ORR is studied using electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) analysis. In all the Nyquist plots, a semicircle has been observed in the high-frequency region and a straight line in the low-frequency region. The Nyquist plot allows the analysis of the interfacial charge transfer processes as well as diffusion processes in the system. All three graphs have been fitted with a similar equivalent circuit shown in Fig. 11
                     a and b. The values of all the fitted parameters are listed in Table 3. The NC helps significantly to reduce the charge transfer resistance (Rct). It is well known that lower Rct always helps to get enhanced ORR activity. The values of Rct in CuO/ZnO/NC-600 (9.19 Ω) is lower than CuO/ZnO (114.50 Ω), and CuO/ZnO/NC (15.07 Ω) (Table 4
                     ). The improved ORR performance of CuO/ZnO/NC-600 has been attributed to the synergistic effect between CuO/ZnO and the nitrogen-doped carbon support.
